      <data key="d5">1753989764</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Reporting Applications">
      <data key="d0">Reporting Applications</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Reporting Applications are software tools or systems that generate reports based on data from the HR.JOB_HISTORY table, often utilizing the JHIST_DEPARTMENT_IX index to efficiently retrieve department-based job history information.&lt;SEP&gt;Reporting applications are software tools that generate reports, often using queries optimized by indexes like LOC_COUNTRY_IX.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1de866b5986aebcccae444bb76f0105b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb684b9b744514893d0d1b99289bbe05</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jhist_department_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.loc_country_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988815</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HR Applications">
      <data key="d0">HR Applications</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">HR Applications are business software solutions that support human resources processes, including querying and managing job history data by department, and benefit from the performance improvements provided by the JHIST_DEPARTMENT_IX index.&lt;SEP&gt;HR applications are software systems that utilize the HR schema, including the HR.JOBS table, for job selection, validation, and other human resources processes.&lt;SEP&gt;Software systems that use HR.JOBS for job selection, validation, and reporting.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-35af4e5a5e00230258378b2941dcb564&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1de866b5986aebcccae444bb76f0105b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e8912ac03211e6d10a671c1a31ccb8e</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jhist_department_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.jobs.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989329</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Department-Based Queries">
      <data key="d0">Department-Based Queries</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Department-Based Queries refer to database queries that filter, join, or sort job history records by the DEPARTMENT_ID column, and are the primary use case for the JHIST_DEPARTMENT_IX index.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1de866b5986aebcccae444bb76f0105b</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jhist_department_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753985439</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Index Properties">
      <data key="d0">Index Properties</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Index Properties are configuration options for the JHIST_DEPARTMENT_IX index, including NOLOGGING (minimal redo/undo logging), NOCOMPRESS (no compression of index entries), and NOPARALLEL (serial index operations), each affecting performance, storage, and recoverability.&lt;SEP&gt;Index Properties refer to the technical settings of HR.JHIST_JOB_IX, including NOLOGGING, NOCOMPRESS, and NOPARALLEL, which affect performance, storage, and recovery.&lt;SEP&gt;Index Properties are the technical settings of the index, such as NOLOGGING, NOCOMPRESS, and NOPARALLEL.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1de866b5986aebcccae444bb76f0105b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db329f300a48c02eb5236b03367fb951&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc3f432e526e12067b6a12ccbff962</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jhist_job_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.jhist_department_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.jhist_employee_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989795</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NOLOGGING">
      <data key="d0">NOLOGGING</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">NOLOGGING is an Oracle database storage specification and index option designed to minimize the generation of redo logs during index creation, rebuilds, and certain maintenance operations. By reducing both redo and undo logging, NOLOGGING significantly improves performance and reduces I/O load, particularly for large data sets and bulk operations, such as those involving indexes like hr.LOC_CITY_IX and hr.LOC_STATE_PROVINCE_IX. This option is especially beneficial when fast index creation is a priority, as it allows for quicker and more efficient index builds and bulk data loads. However, the performance gains come with increased risk: because minimal logging is performed, if a failure occurs during the index creation or maintenance process, the affected index may not be fully recoverable from redo logs and might need to be rebuilt after recovery. NOLOGGING applies specifically to index creation and certain maintenance tasks, not to subsequent DML (Data Manipulation Language) operations. It is most suitable in scenarios where the risk of data loss for the index before backup is acceptable in exchange for improved performance during bulk index operations, and it requires special attention during backup and recovery planning.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7caa66c20d092a335dc8648173fb5354&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fedc09939f22511bb84ca5aa5751c23&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a41048dcaa5356d2ec9a434224117f92&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-410ac6b3623a033ae62dfa51c383d7a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac0843275fead0fc502c43470c04f3a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb684b9b744514893d0d1b99289bbe05&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf21f34bdc08f5a0331c894d66d1eb31&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f93583342dc27c6c3331c90c22264c1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b4c65c6163252963d56c1f1400c52aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51ba69f951ee5b889d1443142c78204b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc3f432e526e12067b6a12ccbff962&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f5b845ca1a4e306071c9c2fa3b01b60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e24ec303a0c36890649afea58f3fecf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db329f300a48c02eb5236b03367fb951&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1de866b5986aebcccae444bb76f0105b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ca92db0127a6ddd811d5e51df59e9bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a2423bebf79f4b25a5ba6899782bf512&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abc6c43b64e9581a394cc085e8662a94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bcb6882954ebc0bf73a53009f4e43c91</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jhist_job_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.jhist_employee_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.emp_manager_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.emp_job_is.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.jhist_department_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.loc_city_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.loc_country_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.emp_name_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.dept_location_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.emp_department_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.loc_state_province_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989771</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NOCOMPRESS">
      <data key="d0">NOCOMPRESS</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">NOCOMPRESS is an Oracle database index option and storage specification that disables key compression for indexes. When the NOCOMPRESS option is applied, each index entry is stored in full without any compression, preserving complete row information for each entry. This approach can increase disk and storage requirements, as no space savings are achieved through compression. However, NOCOMPRESS may improve access speed and query performance for certain workloads, particularly when performance is prioritized over storage conservation. It is often selected for high-cardinality columns, situations where compression does not yield significant space savings, or when avoiding the CPU overhead associated with compression is desirable. By simplifying index access and maintenance, NOCOMPRESS can be beneficial in scenarios where ease of management and performance are more important than minimizing storage usage. This option is commonly used in Oracle databases for indexes such as hr.LOC_CITY_IX or LOC_STATE_PROVINCE_IX, especially when indexed columns have few repeating values. The use of NOCOMPRESS should be carefully considered based on specific workload requirements, as it directly impacts both the storage efficiency and performance characteristics of the index.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7caa66c20d092a335dc8648173fb5354&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fedc09939f22511bb84ca5aa5751c23&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a41048dcaa5356d2ec9a434224117f92&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-410ac6b3623a033ae62dfa51c383d7a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac0843275fead0fc502c43470c04f3a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb684b9b744514893d0d1b99289bbe05&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf21f34bdc08f5a0331c894d66d1eb31&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f93583342dc27c6c3331c90c22264c1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b4c65c6163252963d56c1f1400c52aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51ba69f951ee5b889d1443142c78204b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc3f432e526e12067b6a12ccbff962&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f5b845ca1a4e306071c9c2fa3b01b60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e24ec303a0c36890649afea58f3fecf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db329f300a48c02eb5236b03367fb951&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1de866b5986aebcccae444bb76f0105b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ca92db0127a6ddd811d5e51df59e9bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a2423bebf79f4b25a5ba6899782bf512&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abc6c43b64e9581a394cc085e8662a94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bcb6882954ebc0bf73a53009f4e43c91</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jhist_job_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.jhist_employee_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.emp_manager_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.emp_job_is.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.jhist_department_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.loc_city_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.loc_country_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.emp_name_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.dept_location_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.emp_department_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.loc_state_province_ix.md</data>
