    <node id="COUNTRIES Table">
      <data key="d0">COUNTRIES Table</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The COUNTRIES table is a reference table within the HR schema that stores standardized country information, which is referenced by the LOCATIONS table via the COUNTRY_ID foreign key.&lt;SEP&gt;The COUNTRIES table is a related table in the HR schema that typically references the hr.REGIONS table via REGION_ID as a foreign key. It stores information about countries and their association with regions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b690355f198c13b5e87d1ffcca55ecdb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d57c05e29cac79ec75bdc43f56c5d29</data>
