    <node id="State/Province">
      <data key="d0">State/Province</data>
      <data key="d1">geo</data>
      <data key="d2">State/Province refers to the regional division within a country where a company location is situated, as stored in the STATE_PROVINCE column of the LOCATIONS table.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0d57c05e29cac79ec75bdc43f56c5d29</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.locations.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753985853</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Country">
      <data key="d0">Country</data>
      <data key="d1">geo</data>
      <data key="d2">Country is a geopolitical entity, typically a nation or territory, that is represented in the COUNTRIES table within the HR schema. Each country is identified by a unique country_id and has attributes such as country_name. Countries are grouped under regions, establishing an association via the COUNTRIES table. Additionally, the COUNTRY_ID column in the LOCATIONS table references the country where a specific company location is situated, linking locations to their respective countries. This structure allows countries to be associated with regions and locations within the database.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b690355f198c13b5e87d1ffcca55ecdb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d57c05e29cac79ec75bdc43f56c5d29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89893c024eb2366461dff72cd763aa91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67ba005b5e6c9ddace0480cb68a9b2f1</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.locations.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.emp_details_view.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.regions.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753987455</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Regional Reporting">
      <data key="d0">Regional Reporting</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Regional Reporting is a business process supported by the LOCATIONS table, enabling analytics and reporting on company presence by city, state, or country.&lt;SEP&gt;Regional Reporting is a business process that aggregates and analyzes data by country and region, leveraging the HR.COUNTRIES and HR.REGIONS tables for accurate geographic information.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0d57c05e29cac79ec75bdc43f56c5d29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73f007da0ab621159b7da01edd3c2d4c</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.locations.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.countries.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988954</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Employee Assignment">
      <data key="d0">Employee Assignment</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Employee Assignment is a business process supported by the LOCATIONS table, allowing employees to be associated with specific physical locations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0d57c05e29cac79ec75bdc43f56c5d29</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.locations.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753985856</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Logistics">
      <data key="d0">Logistics</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Logistics is a business process supported by the LOCATIONS table, involving the management of the flow of goods, services, and information between company locations.&lt;SEP&gt;Logistics refers to the business processes supported by the hr.LOCATIONS table, such as shipment, delivery, and resource allocation based on location data.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0d57c05e29cac79ec75bdc43f56c5d29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25b7b3b2770cd1281cfdd6e1a0e9ab43</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.locations.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753985856</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Business Operations">
      <data key="d0">Business Operations</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Business Operations are activities such as reporting, analytics, and application features that require rapid access to location data by state or province, supported by the LOC_STATE_PROVINCE_IX index.&lt;SEP&gt;Business Operations refers to the activities and processes that the LOCATIONS table supports by mapping operations to specific geographic sites.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-51ba69f951ee5b889d1443142c78204b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d57c05e29cac79ec75bdc43f56c5d29</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.loc_state_province_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.locations.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753986936</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Reporting and Analytics">
      <data key="d0">Reporting and Analytics</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Reporting and Analytics are business functions enabled by the LOCATIONS table, allowing analysis of company presence and operations by geographic region.&lt;SEP&gt;Reporting and Analytics refers to business processes and application modules that analyze, aggregate, and present job history data, often leveraging the HR.JHIST_JOB_IX index for performance optimization.&lt;SEP&gt;Reporting and analytics refer to the processes and tools used to aggregate and analyze job history data by job role, supporting business intelligence and HR decision-making.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bcb6882954ebc0bf73a53009f4e43c91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db329f300a48c02eb5236b03367fb951&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d57c05e29cac79ec75bdc43f56c5d29</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jhist_job_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.locations.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753986430</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COUNTRIES">
      <data key="d0">COUNTRIES</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">COUNTRIES is a table commonly referenced in HR or location-based database schemas, typically storing information about countries. The COUNTRY_ID column in hr.LOCATIONS is often a foreign key to this table, supporting referential integrity and enabling joins between location and country data.&lt;SEP&gt;The COUNTRIES table is a reference table in the database that stores valid country codes and related information. It is referenced by the hr.LOCATIONS table via a foreign key to ensure that each location is associated with a valid country.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bb684b9b744514893d0d1b99289bbe05&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25b7b3b2770cd1281cfdd6e1a0e9ab43</data>
