    <node id="Table Dependency">
      <data key="d0">Table Dependency</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Table Dependency refers to the relationships in which certain indexes depend on the existence and structure of specific database tables and their columns. Specifically, Table Dependency includes the reliance of the LOC_CITY_IX index on the hr.LOCATIONS table and its CITY column, as well as the reliance of an index on the hr.LOCATIONS table and its STATE_PROVINCE column for its existence and function. Additionally, Table Dependency encompasses the reliance of the JHIST_EMPLOYEE_IX index on the JOB_HISTORY table and its EMPLOYEE_ID column, as well as the general dependence of indexes on the structure and existence of the JOB_HISTORY table and its EMPLOYEE_ID column. In summary, Table Dependency highlights how indexes such as LOC_CITY_IX and JHIST_EMPLOYEE_IX are functionally and structurally dependent on the presence and configuration of specific tables and columns within a database.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-51ba69f951ee5b889d1443142c78204b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b4c65c6163252963d56c1f1400c52aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc3f432e526e12067b6a12ccbff962</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.loc_state_province_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.loc_city_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.jhist_employee_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989779</data>
    </node>
