    <node id="hr.LOC_CITY_IX">
      <data key="d0">hr.LOC_CITY_IX</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">hr.LOC_CITY_IX is a non-unique, ascending index created on the CITY column of the hr.LOCATIONS table. It is configured with no compression (NOCOMPRESS) and minimal redo logging (NOLOGGING) to optimize query performance for city-based queries. The index is intended for environments where fast creation and query performance are prioritized over recoverability during index creation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a2423bebf79f4b25a5ba6899782bf512</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.loc_city_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753986014</data>
    </node>
