    <node id="Index Fragmentation">
      <data key="d0">Index Fragmentation</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Index Fragmentation refers to the inefficient and disordered organization of index data that occurs over time, typically as a result of data modifications. This condition arises when the logical ordering of index pages no longer matches their physical ordering, leading to degraded database performance. Index Fragmentation requires regular monitoring and periodic maintenance, such as rebuilding or reorganizing the index, to restore efficiency and ensure optimal performance.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-410ac6b3623a033ae62dfa51c383d7a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e24ec303a0c36890649afea58f3fecf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f5b845ca1a4e306071c9c2fa3b01b60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bcb6882954ebc0bf73a53009f4e43c91</data>
