      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">Performance degradation refers to the decline in database or index efficiency, often due to fragmentation or suboptimal configuration, necessitating maintenance actions.&lt;SEP&gt;Performance degradation refers to the slowing down of query or application performance, which may occur if the EMP_DEPARTMENT_IX index is dropped or not maintained.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bcb6882954ebc0bf73a53009f4e43c91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a01dcf1c9756eb26a45470d65ee6f338</data>
