    <node id="START_DATE">
      <data key="d0">START_DATE</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">START_DATE is a required field in the HR.JOB_HISTORY table, representing the beginning of a job assignment period and forming part of the composite primary key.&lt;SEP&gt;START_DATE is the date an employee began a specific job assignment, forming part of the composite primary key in the JOB_HISTORY table and used to distinguish different job assignments for the same employee.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f233a5b64c38c0d8b24476f5ade01458&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f5925672172ca41c13261bbb15e276f</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.job_history.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753986712</data>
    </node>
    <node id="END_DATE">
      <data key="d0">END_DATE</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">END_DATE is a required field in the HR.JOB_HISTORY table, representing the end of a job assignment period. A check constraint ensures END_DATE is after START_DATE.&lt;SEP&gt;END_DATE is the date an employee ended a specific job assignment, used to define the duration of each job history record and validated to be after the START_DATE.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f233a5b64c38c0d8b24476f5ade01458&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f5925672172ca41c13261bbb15e276f</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.job_history.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753986712</data>
    </node>
    <node id="JHIST_EMP_ID_ST_DATE_PK">
      <data key="d0">JHIST_EMP_ID_ST_DATE_PK</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">JHIST_EMP_ID_ST_DATE_PK is the composite primary key constraint on HR.JOB_HISTORY, ensuring each job assignment period per employee is unique based on EMPLOYEE_ID and START_DATE.&lt;SEP&gt;JHIST_EMP_ID_ST_DATE_PK is the primary key constraint on the JOB_HISTORY table, ensuring uniqueness of each job assignment period for an employee by combining EMPLOYEE_ID and START_DATE.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f233a5b64c38c0d8b24476f5ade01458&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f5925672172ca41c13261bbb15e276f</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.job_history.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753986720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="JHIST_DATE_INTERVAL">
      <data key="d0">JHIST_DATE_INTERVAL</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">JHIST_DATE_INTERVAL is a check constraint on HR.JOB_HISTORY that enforces logical consistency by ensuring END_DATE is after START_DATE.&lt;SEP&gt;JHIST_DATE_INTERVAL is a check constraint on the JOB_HISTORY table that enforces END_DATE to be greater than START_DATE, ensuring logical job assignment periods.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f233a5b64c38c0d8b24476f5ade01458&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f5925672172ca41c13261bbb15e276f</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.job_history.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753986720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="JHIST_EMP_FK">
      <data key="d0">JHIST_EMP_FK</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">JHIST_EMP_FK is a foreign key constraint in HR.JOB_HISTORY, ensuring EMPLOYEE_ID values reference valid employees in HR.EMPLOYEES.&lt;SEP&gt;JHIST_EMP_FK is a foreign key constraint linking EMPLOYEE_ID in JOB_HISTORY to EMPLOYEE_ID in the EMPLOYEES table, enforcing referential integrity.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f233a5b64c38c0d8b24476f5ade01458&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f5925672172ca41c13261bbb15e276f</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.job_history.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753986720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="JHIST_JOB_FK">
      <data key="d0">JHIST_JOB_FK</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">JHIST_JOB_FK is a foreign key constraint in HR.JOB_HISTORY, ensuring JOB_ID values reference valid jobs in HR.JOBS.&lt;SEP&gt;JHIST_JOB_FK is a foreign key constraint linking JOB_ID in JOB_HISTORY to JOB_ID in the JOBS table, enforcing referential integrity.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f233a5b64c38c0d8b24476f5ade01458&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f5925672172ca41c13261bbb15e276f</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.job_history.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753986722</data>
    </node>
    <node id="JHIST_DEPT_FK">
      <data key="d0">JHIST_DEPT_FK</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">JHIST_DEPT_FK is a foreign key constraint in HR.JOB_HISTORY, ensuring DEPARTMENT_ID values reference valid departments in HR.DEPARTMENTS if provided.&lt;SEP&gt;JHIST_DEPT_FK is a foreign key constraint linking DEPARTMENT_ID in JOB_HISTORY to DEPARTMENT_ID in the DEPARTMENTS table, enforcing referential integrity.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f233a5b64c38c0d8b24476f5ade01458&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f5925672172ca41c13261bbb15e276f</data>
