    <node id="Department">
      <data key="d0">Department</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">A Department is a functional unit within an organization, such as Administration, Marketing, Purchasing, Human Resources, Shipping, IT, Executive, Public Relations, Sales, Finance, or Accounting. Each Department is represented as an organizational unit in the company’s DEPARTMENTS table, with attributes including a unique department_id (DEPARTMENT_ID), department_name, and location_id. Departments may have an assigned manager and are associated with specific physical locations. Additionally, each Department is linked to employees and locations, serving as a key organizational structure within the company.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2062c94493f296606e14ada3763e1f63&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89893c024eb2366461dff72cd763aa91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67ba005b5e6c9ddace0480cb68a9b2f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f5925672172ca41c13261bbb15e276f</data>
