      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">Media Failure is a potential event where storage hardware fails, and the use of NOLOGGING increases the risk of index data loss before backup in such an event.&lt;SEP&gt;Media failure is a database event where storage hardware fails, potentially causing data loss, especially if NOLOGGING is used and a backup has not yet occurred.&lt;SEP&gt;Media Failure refers to hardware or storage failures that can result in data loss, particularly relevant when NOLOGGING is enabled and a backup has not yet occurred.</data>
