    <node id="hr.LOC_STATE_PROVINCE_IX">
      <data key="d0">hr.LOC_STATE_PROVINCE_IX</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">hr.LOC_STATE_PROVINCE_IX is a standard, non-unique, ascending B-tree index created on the STATE_PROVINCE column of the hr.LOCATIONS table. It is designed to optimize query performance for state/province-based lookups and sorts, with settings such as NOLOGGING, NOCOMPRESS, and NOPARALLEL for performance and operational efficiency. The index is regularly monitored and may be rebuilt as part of database maintenance.</data>
