    <node id="EMP_JOB_IX">
      <data key="d0">EMP_JOB_IX</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">EMP_JOB_IX is a non-unique, single-column B-tree index created on the JOB_ID column of the HR.EMPLOYEES table. Its primary function is to optimize query performance for operations filtering or sorting by job role, supporting HR business processes such as reporting, analytics, payroll, and organizational chart generation. It is configured with NOLOGGING, NOCOMPRESS, and NOPARALLEL properties to balance performance, storage, and maintenance considerations.&lt;SEP&gt;EMP_JOB_IX is an index created on the JOB_ID column of the HR.EMPLOYEES table. It is designed to optimize query performance for operations filtering or sorting by job role. The index uses standard B-tree structure and is configured with Oracle-specific options such as NOLOGGING and NOCOMPRESS, prioritizing fast creation and maintenance over storage efficiency.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-3f5b845ca1a4e306071c9c2fa3b01b60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf21f34bdc08f5a0331c894d66d1eb31</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_job_is.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753987628</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HR applications">
      <data key="d0">HR applications</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">HR applications are business systems that manage employee and department data, integrating with the HR.DEPARTMENTS table for employee management and reporting.&lt;SEP&gt;HR applications are software systems or tools that interact with the HR.EMPLOYEES table, leveraging the EMP_JOB_IX index to efficiently query, report, and analyze employee data by job role.&lt;SEP&gt;HR applications are software systems that utilize the HR schema, including the HR.JOBS table, for job selection, validation, and other human resources processes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cf21f34bdc08f5a0331c894d66d1eb31&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e8912ac03211e6d10a671c1a31ccb8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a837c6cab856c3245b8657e36779634a</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_job_is.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.jobs.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.departments.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989407</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Reporting tools">
      <data key="d0">Reporting tools</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Reporting tools are software platforms or modules used to generate reports and analytics from the HR.EMPLOYEES table, often utilizing the EMP_JOB_IX index for performance in job-based queries.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cf21f34bdc08f5a0331c894d66d1eb31</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_job_is.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753987628</data>
