    <node id="Parallelism">
      <data key="d0">Parallelism</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Parallelism is a database feature that allows operations such as index creation or maintenance to be performed using multiple CPU resources simultaneously, improving speed for large-scale operations.&lt;SEP&gt;Parallelism is a database feature that allows operations such as index creation or rebuild to be performed using multiple processes for increased speed, though it is not used in the current index setup.&lt;SEP&gt;Parallelism refers to the use of multiple processing threads for index operations, disabled in this index by the NOPARALLEL setting.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-3f5b845ca1a4e306071c9c2fa3b01b60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e24ec303a0c36890649afea58f3fecf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09ae56303a408108e3ca8484bf8e0a54</data>
