    <node id="HR.DEPARTMENTS table">
      <data key="d0">HR.DEPARTMENTS table</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The HR.DEPARTMENTS table is a core database entity within the HR schema, representing the structure and organization of business departments. It enforces data integrity through primary and foreign key constraints, supports HR administration, employee assignment, reporting, and integrates with other HR, payroll, finance, and facilities management systems. The table is designed for flexibility and robustness, with mandatory department identifiers and names, and optional manager and location assignments.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a837c6cab856c3245b8657e36779634a</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.departments.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753987889</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EMPLOYEES table">
      <data key="d0">EMPLOYEES table</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The EMPLOYEES table is a referenced database entity that stores employee records, including those who may be assigned as department managers or as members of departments. It is integral to HR processes and referential integrity enforcement.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a837c6cab856c3245b8657e36779634a</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.departments.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753987890</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Primary Key Constraint (DEPT_ID_PK)">
      <data key="d0">Primary Key Constraint (DEPT_ID_PK)</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">DEPT_ID_PK is the primary key constraint on the DEPARTMENT_ID column, ensuring each department is uniquely identifiable.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a837c6cab856c3245b8657e36779634a</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.departments.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753987890</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Foreign Key Constraint (DEPT_LOC_FK)">
      <data key="d0">Foreign Key Constraint (DEPT_LOC_FK)</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">DEPT_LOC_FK is a foreign key constraint on the LOCATION_ID column, guaranteeing that department locations are valid and exist in the LOCATIONS table.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a837c6cab856c3245b8657e36779634a</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.departments.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753987891</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Foreign Key Constraint (DEPT_MGR_FK)">
      <data key="d0">Foreign Key Constraint (DEPT_MGR_FK)</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">DEPT_MGR_FK is a foreign key constraint on the MANAGER_ID column, ensuring that department managers are valid employees in the EMPLOYEES table.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a837c6cab856c3245b8657e36779634a</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.departments.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753987891</data>
    </node>
