    <node id="HR.EMP_MANAGER_IX">
      <data key="d0">HR.EMP_MANAGER_IX</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">HR.EMP_MANAGER_IX is a database index object within the HR schema, designed to optimize queries filtering or joining on the MANAGER_ID column of the HR.EMPLOYEES table. It is a standard B-tree index with options NOLOGGING, NOCOMPRESS, and NOPARALLEL, and is used to support efficient retrieval of employees by manager, facilitating organizational chart generation, management reporting, and hierarchical queries.&lt;SEP&gt;HR.EMP_MANAGER_IX is a non-unique, non-compressed, non-parallel, and minimally logged database index on the MANAGER_ID column of the HR.EMPLOYEES table. It is designed to optimize performance for queries involving employee-manager relationships, especially in environments with frequent bulk data operations. The index is critical for HR operations, reporting, and analytics, but requires careful maintenance and consideration in backup and recovery planning.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ac0843275fead0fc502c43470c04f3a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-410ac6b3623a033ae62dfa51c383d7a0</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_manager_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988357</data>
    </node>
