    <node id="EMP_NAME_IX">
      <data key="d0">EMP_NAME_IX</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">EMP_NAME_IX is a database index created on the HR.EMPLOYEES table, specifically on the LAST_NAME and FIRST_NAME columns. It is non-unique, non-compressed, non-parallel, and uses minimal logging. The index is designed to optimize name-based queries, providing fast lookups and alphabetical listings for employee data. It is a critical performance object in HR systems, with low maintenance overhead and configuration choices that support efficient bulk operations and predictable resource usage.&lt;SEP&gt;EMP_NAME_IX is a database index in the HR schema, designed to optimize query performance on the HR.EMPLOYEES table, specifically for filtering and sorting by LAST_NAME and FIRST_NAME columns. It is a standard B-tree index with options NOLOGGING, NOCOMPRESS, and NOPARALLEL, and is used to accelerate employee name lookups and alphabetical listings in HR and personnel management systems.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-abc6c43b64e9581a394cc085e8662a94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ca92db0127a6ddd811d5e51df59e9bb</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_name_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988521</data>
    </node>
