    <node id="Bulk Data Load">
      <data key="d0">Bulk Data Load</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">Bulk Data Load is an event or process where large volumes of data are inserted into the EMPLOYEES table, during which NOLOGGING may be used to improve performance.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0ca92db0127a6ddd811d5e51df59e9bb</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_name_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988530</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Table Drop">
      <data key="d0">Table Drop</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">Table Drop is the event of deleting the EMPLOYEES table, which automatically results in the dropping of the EMP_NAME_IX index.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0ca92db0127a6ddd811d5e51df59e9bb</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_name_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988534</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Table Permissions">
      <data key="d0">Table Permissions</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Table Permissions are security settings that govern access to the EMPLOYEES table and, by extension, to the EMP_NAME_IX index.&lt;SEP&gt;Table permissions are security settings that govern access to the EMPLOYEES and DEPARTMENTS tables, indirectly affecting access to the EMP_DEPARTMENT_IX index.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a01dcf1c9756eb26a45470d65ee6f338&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ca92db0127a6ddd811d5e51df59e9bb</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_department_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.emp_name_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988672</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Parallel DML">
      <data key="d0">Parallel DML</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Parallel DML refers to performing data manipulation operations in parallel, which is disabled for EMP_NAME_IX by the NOPARALLEL option.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0ca92db0127a6ddd811d5e51df59e9bb</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_name_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988541</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CPU Overhead">
      <data key="d0">CPU Overhead</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">CPU Overhead refers to the additional processing required for features like key compression, which is avoided in EMP_NAME_IX by using NOCOMPRESS.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0ca92db0127a6ddd811d5e51df59e9bb</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_name_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988541</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Index Size">
      <data key="d0">Index Size</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Index Size refers to the amount of disk space used by EMP_NAME_IX, which may be larger due to NOCOMPRESS.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0ca92db0127a6ddd811d5e51df59e9bb</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_name_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988541</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Application User Experience">
      <data key="d0">Application User Experience</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Application User Experience is improved by EMP_NAME_IX, as it enables faster employee searches and listings in HR applications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0ca92db0127a6ddd811d5e51df59e9bb</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_name_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988541</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HR systems">
      <data key="d0">HR systems</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">HR systems are information systems or software platforms used by organizations to manage human resources data, including employee records, queries, and reporting. They rely on optimized database structures for performance.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-abc6c43b64e9581a394cc085e8662a94</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_name_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988543</data>
    </node>
