      <data key="d0">DML Volume</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">DML Volume refers to the frequency and amount of Data Manipulation Language (DML) operations-such as INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE-on the HR.EMPLOYEES table, which can affect index fragmentation and maintenance needs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a41048dcaa5356d2ec9a434224117f92</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.emp_department_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988679</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Backup Strategies">
      <data key="d0">Backup Strategies</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Backup Strategies are operational plans and procedures to ensure that database objects, including indexes, are properly backed up to prevent data loss, especially important when NOLOGGING is used.&lt;SEP&gt;Backup Strategies are plans and procedures to ensure data recoverability, especially important when using NOLOGGING settings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a41048dcaa5356d2ec9a434224117f92&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e24ec303a0c36890649afea58f3fecf</data>
