    <node id="LOC_COUNTRY_IX">
      <data key="d0">LOC_COUNTRY_IX</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">LOC_COUNTRY_IX is a database index in the hr schema, designed to optimize query performance for operations involving the COUNTRY_ID column in the hr.LOCATIONS table. It is a standard B-tree index with options NOLOGGING, NOCOMPRESS, and NOPARALLEL, and is used to accelerate lookups, joins, and filtering operations by country. It supports business scenarios such as generating country-based location lists, enforcing referential integrity, and supporting foreign key relationships.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bb684b9b744514893d0d1b99289bbe05</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.loc_country_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988800</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Joins">
      <data key="d0">Joins</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Joins are database operations that combine rows from two or more tables, such as hr.LOCATIONS and COUNTRIES, often using COUNTRY_ID and benefiting from the LOC_COUNTRY_IX index.&lt;SEP&gt;Joins refer to SQL operations that combine rows from two or more tables, such as between JOB_HISTORY and EMPLOYEES on EMPLOYEE_ID, often optimized by indexes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5e24ec303a0c36890649afea58f3fecf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb684b9b744514893d0d1b99289bbe05</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jhist_employee_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.loc_country_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989801</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Aggregations">
      <data key="d0">Aggregations</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Aggregations are database operations that summarize data, such as grouping locations by COUNTRY_ID, which are optimized by the LOC_COUNTRY_IX index.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bb684b9b744514893d0d1b99289bbe05</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.loc_country_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988815</data>
    </node>
    <node id="hr.LOC_COUNTRY_IX">
      <data key="d0">hr.LOC_COUNTRY_IX</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">hr.LOC_COUNTRY_IX is a standard, non-unique B-tree index created on the COUNTRY_ID column of the hr.LOCATIONS table. It is designed to optimize query performance for country-based lookups, with options set to minimize logging and avoid compression or parallelism during creation. The index is periodically rebuilt or analyzed to maintain performance and is a key enabler for business processes and applications that access location data by country.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-09ae56303a408108e3ca8484bf8e0a54</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.loc_country_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988822</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Country-based Lookups">
      <data key="d0">Country-based Lookups</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Country-based lookups are queries or operations that retrieve data based on country information, optimized by the hr.LOC_COUNTRY_IX index.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-09ae56303a408108e3ca8484bf8e0a54</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.loc_country_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988824</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Serial Index Creation and Maintenance">
      <data key="d0">Serial Index Creation and Maintenance</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">Serial index creation and maintenance refers to the process of building and periodically maintaining the hr.LOC_COUNTRY_IX index without parallelism, ensuring ongoing performance and reliability.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-09ae56303a408108e3ca8484bf8e0a54</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.loc_country_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988824</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Applications">
      <data key="d0">Applications</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Applications are software systems that access location data by country, benefiting from the performance enabled by the hr.LOC_COUNTRY_IX index.&lt;SEP&gt;Applications refers to business or software applications that query employee job history data, benefiting from the performance improvements provided by the JHIST_EMPLOYEE_IX index.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5e24ec303a0c36890649afea58f3fecf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09ae56303a408108e3ca8484bf8e0a54</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jhist_employee_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.loc_country_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989799</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Function-based Index">
      <data key="d0">Function-based Index</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Function-based index is an advanced database indexing feature not used in hr.LOC_COUNTRY_IX.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-09ae56303a408108e3ca8484bf8e0a54</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.loc_country_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988827</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Unique Index">
      <data key="d0">Unique Index</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Unique index is an advanced database indexing feature not used in hr.LOC_COUNTRY_IX.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-09ae56303a408108e3ca8484bf8e0a54</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.loc_country_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988827</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HR.COUNTRIES Table">
      <data key="d0">HR.COUNTRIES Table</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">The HR.COUNTRIES table is a core reference table within the HR schema of a database, designed to store and standardize information about countries relevant to the organization's business operations. It supports internationalization, regional reporting, referential integrity, and acts as a master data source for country information in integrations with other systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The HR.COUNTRIES table is a foundational reference table within the HR database schema, designed to store standardized country information. It enforces data integrity through primary and foreign key constraints, supports business processes such as address management and regional reporting, and is integrated with external systems for country code validation. The table is characterized by low write and high read operations, with changes logged for recoverability and auditing.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e34db40cf2365e32f299f601d34d886a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73f007da0ab621159b7da01edd3c2d4c</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.countries.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988946</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COUNTRY_NAME">
      <data key="d0">COUNTRY_NAME</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">COUNTRY_NAME is a column in the HR.COUNTRIES table, storing the full name of the country. It is a variable-length string up to 40 bytes and is optional (nullable).</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e34db40cf2365e32f299f601d34d886a</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.countries.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988946</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HR.REGIONS Table">
      <data key="d0">HR.REGIONS Table</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">The HR.REGIONS table is a related reference table in the HR schema, containing region data. It is referenced by the REGION_ID foreign key in the HR.COUNTRIES table to support hierarchical geographic organization.&lt;SEP&gt;The HR.REGIONS table is another reference table in the HR schema, containing region information. It is referenced by the HR.COUNTRIES table via a foreign key to enforce valid region assignments for countries.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e34db40cf2365e32f299f601d34d886a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73f007da0ab621159b7da01edd3c2d4c</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.countries.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753988946</data>
    </node>
    <node id="geo">
      <data key="d0">geo</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">The geo category refers to the geographical information managed by the HR.COUNTRIES table, including country and region data used for reporting, analytics, and compliance.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e34db40cf2365e32f299f601d34d886a</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.countries.md</data>
