    <node id="HR.JOBS Table">
      <data key="d0">HR.JOBS Table</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The HR.JOBS table is a core reference table in the HR schema, defining all valid job roles and their associated salary ranges. It enforces data integrity through primary key and not null constraints, supports key HR business processes, and is designed for integration with other HR data structures. It is used for job selection, validation, and auditing, and is referenced by employee and job history tables.&lt;SEP&gt;The HR.JOBS table is a database object within the HR schema, serving as the master reference for all job roles in the organization. It defines valid job titles, associated minimum and maximum salary ranges, and enforces job-related business rules. It is foundational for HR processes such as hiring, compensation planning, and organizational structuring.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-35af4e5a5e00230258378b2941dcb564&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e8912ac03211e6d10a671c1a31ccb8e</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jobs.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989297</data>
    </node>
    <node id="JOB_TITLE">
      <data key="d0">JOB_TITLE</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">JOB_TITLE is a column in the HR.JOBS table representing the descriptive title of each job (e.g., AD_VP, FI_ACCOUNTANT). It is required and used for display, reporting, and selection in applications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-35af4e5a5e00230258378b2941dcb564</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jobs.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989297</data>
    </node>
