    <node id="HR.JOBS table">
      <data key="d0">HR.JOBS table</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The HR.JOBS table is a core reference table within the HR schema of a database, responsible for defining all valid job roles and their associated salary ranges. It enforces data integrity through primary key and not null constraints, supports HR business processes, and is integrated with other HR data structures. The table is used for job selection, validation, and auditing, and is referenced by employee and job history tables.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2e8912ac03211e6d10a671c1a31ccb8e</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jobs.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989405</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Employee tables">
      <data key="d0">Employee tables</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Employee tables are database tables within the HR schema that store information about employees. They are joined with the HR.JOBS table to retrieve job details and are integral to HR operations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2e8912ac03211e6d10a671c1a31ccb8e</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jobs.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989407</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Job history tables">
      <data key="d0">Job history tables</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Job history tables are part of the HR schema and track changes in employees' job assignments over time. They reference the HR.JOBS table to maintain accurate job records.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2e8912ac03211e6d10a671c1a31ccb8e</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jobs.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989407</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Job roles">
