    <node id="JHIST_EMPLOYEE_IX">
      <data key="d0">JHIST_EMPLOYEE_IX</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">JHIST_EMPLOYEE_IX is an index created on the EMPLOYEE_ID column of the HR.JOB_HISTORY table. It is designed to optimize query performance for employee-centric queries, particularly those joining JOB_HISTORY and EMPLOYEES tables. The index uses NOLOGGING, NOCOMPRESS, and NOPARALLEL settings, prioritizing performance and storage efficiency, but with considerations for recoverability and maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;JHIST_EMPLOYEE_IX is an index object within the HR schema of a database, designed to optimize data retrieval operations on the JOB_HISTORY table, specifically for queries filtering or joining on the EMPLOYEE_ID column. It is a standard B-tree index with NOLOGGING, NOCOMPRESS, and NOPARALLEL properties, enhancing performance for HR reporting, auditing, and employee management processes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5e24ec303a0c36890649afea58f3fecf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc3f432e526e12067b6a12ccbff962</data>
      <data key="d4">hr.jhist_employee_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1753989754</data>
    </node>
