    <edge source="NOLOGGING" target="Redo Log">
      <data key="d6">39.0</data>
      <data key="d7">NOLOGGING is a database option that reduces redo log generation and usage during index creation and maintenance operations. By minimizing the amount of redo log produced, NOLOGGING can improve performance during these operations. However, this reduction in redo log generation also impacts recovery options, as less information is available for database recovery in the event of a failure. Therefore, while NOLOGGING can enhance performance during index operations, it may compromise the ability to fully recover data, affecting both recovery and performance considerations related to redo logs.&lt;SEP&gt;NOLOGGING reduces redo log generation during index operations, affecting recovery and performance.</data>
      <data key="d8">logging,performance,performance tuning,recovery</data>
      <data key="d9">chunk-51ba69f951ee5b889d1443142c78204b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ca92db0127a6ddd811d5e51df59e9bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc3f432e526e12067b6a12ccbff962&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bcb6882954ebc0bf73a53009f4e43c91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db329f300a48c02eb5236b03367fb951</data>
      <data key="d10">hr.jhist_job_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.loc_state_province_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.jhist_employee_ix.md&lt;SEP&gt;hr.emp_name_ix.md</data>
      <data key="d11">1753989814</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NOLOGGING" target="Recovery">
      <data key="d6">7.0</data>
      <data key="d7">Indexes created with NOLOGGING may not be fully recoverable from redo logs in case of failure during creation.</data>
