    <edge source="NOLOGGING" target="Backup">
      <data key="d6">28.0</data>
      <data key="d7">Backup and NOLOGGING are closely related in database management practices. When NOLOGGING is used, it increases the risk of data loss for indexes in the event of a failure before the next backup is performed. This is because NOLOGGING operations do not generate sufficient redo information to fully recover the affected data structures, such as indexes, in case of a failure. Therefore, performing a backup after NOLOGGING operations is crucial to ensure the recoverability of the index and to mitigate the risk of data loss. Regular backups are essential whenever NOLOGGING is used to maintain data integrity and protect against potential failures.</data>
      <data key="d8">data protection,data recovery,recovery,risk management</data>
      <data key="d9">chunk-a01dcf1c9756eb26a45470d65ee6f338&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51ba69f951ee5b889d1443142c78204b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf21f34bdc08f5a0331c894d66d1eb31&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc3f432e526e12067b6a12ccbff962</data>
