    <edge source="Manager" target="Employee">
      <data key="d6">36.0</data>
      <data key="d7">An Employee is an individual who may have a Manager, as indicated by the manager_id field. A Manager is a specific type of Employee who is assigned to oversee a department and supervise other employees. This supervisory relationship is represented in the EMPLOYEES table through a self-referencing foreign key, where the manager_id field references the employee_id. Thus, the Manager-Employee relationship is modeled as a self-referencing relationship within the Employee entity, allowing employees to supervise other employees within the organization.</data>
      <data key="d8">hierarchy,organizational hierarchy,reporting,role,supervision</data>
      <data key="d9">chunk-2062c94493f296606e14ada3763e1f63&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89893c024eb2366461dff72cd763aa91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-905f1da660f25673e4fb9f549742b9dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67ba005b5e6c9ddace0480cb68a9b2f1</data>
